h2 "fab"

em "Posted: August 18 2010"

p "Dutch lessons in Wageningen"

p "I would certainly recommend this teacher to anyone who would like to start a proper Dutch course or improve his/her Dutch. I find private lessons much more profitable than group courses, that's why I had chosen this teacher. I then realized that she spends much more time for you than just the typical one or two hours per week for the lessons. With simple conversations she figures out what your level is, what may be potential obstacles in the beginning (e.g. you being too concerned about picking up every single detail of the grammar, but I am probably an isolated case) and what the best road for you to improve. Between the lessons, she constantly searches newspapers and web sites for articles and especially training material which helps you in the learning process. She is always happy to answer questions via e-email and start a profitable discussion over a topic. She also encourages the student to be curious about the language and to explore various and inexpensive learning media available on the internet. Dus, uitstekend. And. most important: during the lesson you get a cup of tea.."

